Here&#x27;s a couple of interesting Perl alternatives:<p><pre><code>  my @files = map { IO::File->new($_->[0], $_->[1]) || die $! } 
              ([shift, &#x27;r&#x27;], [shift, &#x27;w&#x27;]);
  $files[1]->print( sort $files[0]->getlines );
  $_->close for @files;
</code></pre>
And...<p><pre><code>  use autodie;
  open my $out, &#x27;>&#x27;, $ARGV[1];
  print {$out} sort do {open my $in, &#x27;<&#x27;, $ARGV[0]; <$in>};</code></pre>
